com.fluidops.fedx.evaluation.concurrent

Interface ParallelExecutor<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ControlledWorkerBoundJoin, ControlledWorkerJoin, ControlledWorkerUnion, JoinExecutorBase, ParallelServiceExecutor, SynchronousBoundJoin, SynchronousJoin, SynchronousWorkerUnion, UnionExecutorBase, WorkerUnionBase

    public interface ParallelExecutor<T>
extends java.lang.Runnable
    Interface for any parallel cursor, i.e. result iterations. Implementations can act as control for scheduler implementations, e.g. ControlledWorkerScheduler. The common use case is to pass results from the scheduler to the controlling result iteration.
    Author:
    Andreas Schwarte
    See Also:
    JoinExecutorBase, UnionExecutorBase
